en: El ingenioso hidalgo don Quijote de la Mancha
Por el otro iba echando el vino.

In the center, the innkeeper helping don Quixote to drink with a cane through his helmet; on the left, both party grils (doña Tolosa and doña Molinera); background, a boy with a lamp (taken from the scene of don Quixote knighted), and the swineherd accurate to Cervantes' text; "llegó acaso a la venta un castrador de puercos, y así como llegó sonó su silbato de cañas cuatro o cinco veces" (2:1).Acceptable engraving, but poor printing/inking.

1 - Plate I.2 - Based on José Rivelles' design for Madrid: Imprenta Real, 1819; the distribution of some figures has been changed.3 - Same plate first engraved for Madrid: Imp. de Miguel de Burgos, 1826; also in Madrid: Establecimiento Tipográfico; Gabinete Literario, 1844.
Alzándose como pudo se abrazó con maritornes.
16.2 Episode of Maritornes16.3 DQ fights with muleteer

Well-known scene since Savery (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657); in the center, Sancho attacked by Maritornes and the muleteer; from the right, the innkeeper arrives kicking Maritornes with his leg; on the left, don Quixote gesticulating on his broken bed.Acceptable engraving, but not remarkable.

1 - Plate II.2 - Turned copy after José Rivelles' design for Madrid: Imprenta Real, 1819.3 - Same plate first engraved for Madrid: Imp. de Miguel de Burgos, 1826; also in Madrid: Establecimiento Tipográfico; Gabinete Literario, 1844.
Y apenas hubo caido cuando fué sobre él el estudiante.

In Sierra Morena, the goatherd seizes Cardenio to prevent him from kicking don Quixote and Sancho; see their gestures of force (the goatherd and Cardenio) and almost arrogance (Sancho).Acceptable engraving, but not remarkable.

De aqui no me levanto hasta que vuestra bondad me otorgue un don.

In the foreground, Micomicona knelt before don Quixote, who takes her hand to stand her up; on the right, the barber disguised with a fake beard and, on the left, Sancho.In the background, the priest and Cardenio hidden; on the left, don Quixote's arms.Acceptable engraving, but not remarkable.

Tente ladron, malandrin, follon que aqui te tengo.

The innkeeper, holding a lamp and followed by the priest, the barber and Cardenio(?), enters don Quixote's room and encounters the knight asleep, in shirt, with a blanket around his arm, and attacking several wine-skins with his sword; aside, Sancho searching Pandafilando's head.Quite acceptable engraving.

Con todo esto tiraba de su brazo por ver si podia soltarse.
43.2 Maritornes and innkeeper’s daughter hang DQ from window by a hand43.3 Four travelers arrive at inn

Don Quixote hanging by his hand tied to the inn window; on the left, Rocinante smelling one of the mares of the newly-arrived travelers (servants of don Luis' father); on the right, the innkeeper and other of the travelers on horseback.Quite acceptable engraving.

Muger mia, si Dios quisiera, bien me holgara yo de no estar tan contento como muestro.
5.1 SP speaks with his wife Teresa

Sancho explains to his wife, Teresa, his decision about a new sally; Teresa gesticulates arguing: "sin gobierno salistéis del vientre de vuestra madre, sin gobierno habéis vivido hasta ahora, y sin gobierno os iréis o os llevarán a la sepultura" (5:2).Quite acceptable engraving.

Y con devoto corazon y casi lágrimas le besó los pies una y muchas veces.
16.1 Encounter with knight of the green coat, Don Diego de Miranda
Sancho decides to kiss don Diego de Miranda's feet, thinking that he is almost a saint; don Quixote observes him.Quite acceptable engraving.
